  coaching_execution = '{"movement_description":"Perform Rear-Foot-Elevated Split Squat with attention to hip flexion, knee flexion, hip extension, then reset into a stance or position that would allow another kick, strike, or ball action.","setup":["Set up with bench, dumbbells and enough open space for the athlete to move, pivot, and stop without crowding.","Explain the intended phase and quality gate before the first rep so the athlete knows whether this is access, skill, output, strength, resilience, conditioning, or restore work.","Establish stance foot pressure, rib-pelvis position, and a safe return/reset position before adding speed, load, target, or partner input.","Connect the drill to support-leg force, plant-leg strength so the athlete understands the transfer target without rushing the movement."],"execution_steps":["Start each rep from a balanced setup with the trunk braced and the working foot connected to the floor.","Lower or load through the intended joint action without twisting the knee, arch, pelvis, or low back to steal range.","Drive through the working leg or trunk line with controlled intent while keeping the target tissues doing the work.","Reset breathing and alignment between reps; add load only when the same positions repeat."],"coach_cues":["Front leg does the work; pelvis stays level.","Own the support foot.","Ribs and pelvis stay organized.","Reset before the next rep."],"common_faults":["Chasing range or speed before control","Support foot collapsing or twisting","Leaning through the low back","Letting the kick or movement finish in a poor stance"],"breathing_cues":["Exhale to organize the ribs before effort.","Do not hold breath unless specifically bracing for a loaded strength rep.","Recover nasal or calm breathing between quality attempts."],"quality_gate":"A rep counts only if Rear-Foot-Elevated Split Squat keeps pain-free range, organized breathing, clean support-foot pressure, controlled hip/trunk position, and a safe reset tha